title: 'Favourite city': Jadeja shares stylish pictures; Team India in England for Test series

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Mani Ratnam and Kamal Haasan's 'Thug Life' experienced a slow start at the box office, earning Rs 30.15 crore in India over three days. After a significant drop on Friday, Saturday showed a modest increase, fueled by Tamil Nadu occupancy, especially in Chennai. However, the film struggles in the Hindi belt, facing challenges in connecting with North Indian audiences due to underwhelming reviews.
title: Thug Life day 3: Kamal Haasan film sees small uptick | Rs 30.15 crore collected

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Despite the loss in the final to Royal Challengers Bengaluru, Punjab Kings earned praise for an impressive campaign under Ricky Ponting. The Australia legend opened up about his aggression during games and the way he switches back to being cool outside of cricket. PBKS co-owner Preity Zinta was handed a rare offer by the coach.
title: 'You need to come sit in dugout': Ponting to Preity Zinta, justifies aggressive nature on pitch

author: TNN
description: In a shocking incident in Bengaluru, M Shankar surrendered to Suryanagar police, carrying his wife S Manasa's severed head on his scooter. He confessed to killing her after a dispute over an alleged affair. The couple, both factory workers, had a three-year-old daughter. Neighbors reported hearing a violent altercation before the gruesome act.
title: 'I have come to surrender': Bengaluru man beheads wife after fight over affair

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: After Royal Challengers Bengaluru's historic IPL victory in 2025, Virat Kohli's remarks ignited widespread discussion. Following RCB's final win against Punjab Kings, Kohli emphasised his commitment to all-round contribution. He stated his desire to give his all on the field until he retires, highlighting his aversion to being just an 'impact player'.
title: 'Can't play as impact player': Kohli's statement sparks speculation - was he targeting someone?

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Following RCB's triumph in the IPL final, captain Rajat Patidar announced that the win was dedicated to RCB's trusted talisman Virat Kohli, who has been with the team since the start of the competition in 2008. The captain was also spotted breaking a tradition in the final and urged Kohli to take center stage in the celebrations.
title: IPL 2025: Patidar breaks tradition for Kohli after RCB win — Watch the viral video

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Al-Qaeda's Yemen branch leader, Saad bin Atef al-Awlaki, threatened Donald Trump and Elon Musk over the Gaza conflict in his first public appearance since assuming leadership in 2024. He urged lone-wolf militants to assassinate leaders in Egypt, Jordan, and Gulf Arab nations, while the group seeks to reclaim relevance amidst the Houthi's growing popularity by portraying concern for Gaza.
title: 'No red lines': Al-Qaeda Yemen threatens Trump, Musk; uses Gaza as rallying cry

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce, despite recent public appearances, navigate the shadow of the Blake Lively-Justin Baldoni legal situation. Sources reveal Kelce is Swift's support system amidst the drama, influencing their preference for Florida's privacy over New York. The couple briefly halted joint appearances post-Super Bowl LIX due to heightened attention.
title: Is Taylor still friends with Blake? Fallout from Baldoni lawsuit continues

author: TNN
description: The construction of the world's highest cable-supported single-arch bridge on the Chenab River faced significant hurdles, including a series of Public Interest Litigations (PILs) filed in courts since 2008-09. These PILs challenged the project's alignment, cost, and methodology, causing delays.
title: Chenab river link: Besides engineering challenges, world's highest rail bridge overcame legal hurdles too

author: SOUMITRA BOSE
description: Maharashtra's C-60 commandos are preparing for a final assault on Abujmarh, the Maoist headquarters, following the CM's visit. Simultaneously, Odisha police are intensifying searches in Sambalpur forests due to an influx of Maoists from Chhattisgarh. The operation aims to eliminate the Maoist presence, focusing on key leaders like Bhupathi and Kosa, who are evading capture in the challenging terrain.
title: Commandos plan final assault on Maoist top guns in Abujmarh

author: TNN
description: Recent World Bank data reveals a significant decline in India's extreme poverty rate, dropping from 27.1% in 2011-12 to 5.3% in 2022-23, lifting nearly 270 million people out of extreme poverty. This reduction is attributed to updated poverty line definitions and improved household survey data. Free food transfers and a narrowing rural-urban poverty gap also contributed to this progress.
title: Despite World Bank raising threshold, India achieves big dip in extreme poverty

author: BHARTI JAIN
description: Election Commission officials have strongly refuted Rahul Gandhi's claims of "fixing" the Maharashtra polls, dismissing them as absurd and disrespectful to the electoral process. The EC emphasized the transparency of the elections, highlighting the involvement of Congress's own booth level agents in the process.
title: Rahul's claims absurd, bring into disrepute Cong's own polling reps, say EC officials

author: TNN
description: Following the tragic stampede outside Chinnaswamy Stadium during RCB's IPL victory celebrations, the Karnataka government has appointed retired Justice John Michael D'Cunha to lead a probe, demanding a report within a month. Alongside judicial and magisterial inquiries, the CID has taken over the criminal investigation, seizing evidence and questioning KSCA staff.
title: Retired HC judge John Michael D'Cunha who convicted Jaya to probe Bengaluru stampede

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump threatened federal intervention in Los Angeles due to protests against immigration raids, criticizing Governor Newsom and Mayor Bass. Clashes escalated in Paramount as agents deployed tear gas, leading to arrests, including union leader David Huerta. Senator Schumer condemned Huerta's arrest, alleging suppression of free speech, while Homeland Security vowed prosecution for obstructing law enforcement.
title: 'Riots, looters...will be solved': Trump deploys 2k troops as LA unrest grows

author: ABHAY
description: In a shocking incident, Satendra Yadav has been arrested for allegedly murdering his girlfriend, Neelesh, in Delhi. Motivated by a financial dispute and suspicions of infidelity, Yadav strangled Neelesh, packed her body in a suitcase, and disposed of it in Hapur, Uttar Pradesh.
title: Man kills partner in fit of rage; dumps body in suitcase in UP

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: Musk hit Scott Bessent's ribcage after being called 'fraud', Trump called it 'too much'

author: TNN
description: Mangaluru police apprehended Chalasani Monica Choudary, a postgraduate medical student, for orchestrating a hoax bomb threat to a private hospital. The incident occurred on June 4th, with Choudary intending to evade a seminar presentation. Ironically, she also filed a complaint about the threat, but technical analysis exposed her involvement, leading to her arrest and the seizure of her mobile phone.
title: A PG medic wanted to skip a seminar. So she issued a hoax bomb threat

author: SACHIN PARASHAR
description: External Affairs Minister Jaishankar conveyed to UK's David Lammy India's firm stance against equating perpetrators of terrorism with its victims, emphasizing zero tolerance. Lammy condemned the Pahalgam attack and pledged support against cross-border terrorism. Discussions also covered the India-UK Free Trade Agreement, deepened strategic partnership, and enhanced cooperation across various sectors, including trade, defense, and technology.
title: Can't club terror-backers with victims: EAM Jaishankar to UK's Lammy

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Colombian presidential candidate Miguel Uribe was shot during a campaign event in Bogotá's Fontibón district, as confirmed by the national police. Bogotá Mayor Carlos Galán reported that Uribe is receiving emergency medical care, with the city's hospitals on alert. The suspected attacker has been arrested.
title: Colombian presidential candidate Miguel Uribe shot during campaign; attacker arrested

author: MALATHY IYER
description: Payal, a 27-year-old Mahim resident, experienced a heart attack, shocking her family due to her age and the perceived protection women have during childbearing years. Doctors identified contraceptive pills, prescribed for her polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS), as the likely culprit.
title: Contraceptive pills linked to heart attack in young woman with PCOS

author: CHETHAN KUMAR
description: The Axiom- mission (Ax-4) astronauts, including India's Group Captain Shubhanshu Shukla, are participating in the Suite Ride experiment, a medical study exploring glucose behavior and insulin stability in microgravity. This research aims to validate technologies that could potentially allow insulin-dependent diabetics to safely undertake spaceflight in the future.
title: Glucose in space: Ax-4 crew to play key role in diabetes study

author: TNN
description: The Central Consumer Protection Authority (CCPA) has instructed e-commerce platforms to conduct self-audits within three months to detect and remove 'dark patterns' that manipulate consumers. Platforms are encouraged to provide self-declarations confirming their compliance. A joint working group has been established to monitor violations and promote consumer awareness.
title: Govt cracks whip on dark patterns, sets e-commerce companies 3-month deadline

author: MANTHAN K MEHTA
description: In the heart of Mumbai's Dharavi, women like Alaguthai Thangapandi are the unsung heroes, crafting fresh idlis daily to feed the city. Sourcing ingredients meticulously, they face challenges like poor infrastructure and monsoon disruptions. With the Dharavi Redevelopment Project underway, they hope for better kitchens and dignified living conditions to expand their culinary contributions.
title: Hope steams up among Dharavi’s idli-makers over redevelopment plan

author: TNN
description: India reported four new Covid-19 fatalities, including a pregnant woman, raising the year's death toll to 59 with 5,755 active cases. In response to rising cases and deaths, the central government is conducting mock drills to assess Covid preparedness. States are ensuring the availability of essential resources, while surveillance units monitor influenza-like illnesses and severe acute respiratory illnesses.
title: India records 4 fresh Covid fatalities; toll rises to 59

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Manipur government has suspended internet services in five districts, including Imphal West and East, for five days due to escalating law and order concerns. This decision follows protests sparked by the arrest of an Arambai Tenggol leader, alongside intensified security operations that led to the arrest of militants and recovery of weapons. The state remains tense amidst ongoing ethnic conflict.
title: Manipur suspends internet for five days in five districts amid unrest

author: VIMAL BHATIA
description: Rajasthan Police discovered Shakur Khan's passport, revealing multiple trips to Pakistan, including one in March 2025. Khan, an assistant administrative officer, is accused of aiding Pakistani visa applications and collaborating with a Pakistani official expelled from India. Over 25 individuals who received visa assistance are being interrogated as the investigation expands, focusing on Khan's espionage activities and connections.
title: Passport of Rajasthan staffer held for spying reveals 4 Pakistan trips

author: TNN
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi highlighted the transformation of the agriculture sector over the past 11 years, emphasizing increased farmer prosperity through initiatives like PM-Kisan and improved MSP. Agricultural exports have surged, and access to affordable finance has expanded significantly. The government's focus on soil health, irrigation, and crop insurance has bolstered foodgrain production and secured farmer incomes.
title: PM Modi: Govt initiatives over 11 years helped farmers prosper

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: 'These are Muslim values, these are Canadian values': PM Mark Carney

author: TNN
description: Goa's Health Minister, Vishwajit Rane, addressed criticism after publicly reprimanding a Goa Medical College chief medical officer. While admitting his tone was excessive and promising to avoid similar approaches, Rane defended his intervention, citing a patient denied care.
title: ‘Tone could’ve been more measured’: Goa minister defends GMC outburst

author: RAHUL GAYAKWAD
description: Amidst a sensitive environment, the Vishalgad Urs faces restrictions as the archaeological department prohibits it, citing the fort's protected status. Despite this, trustees affirm the Urs will proceed from June 8-10, adhering to high court orders and administrative guidelines. Heightened security measures are in place following warnings, with fort access limited to 9am-5pm, ensuring a low-key observance of traditional rituals.
title: ‘No night stay’: Urs at Shivaji-era fort goes low-key after court restrictions

author: TNN
description: In Chennai, Doctor Santosh Kumar was arrested for the murder of Nithya. Nithya blackmailed him for money. She threatened to release his private pictures. Santosh gave her sedative-laced alcohol. He then smothered her. He stole gold jewellery from her home. Police found the jewellery with a neighbor. They are investigating if Nithya blackmailed others.
title: Blackmailed with nudes, doctor kills woman in Chennai

author: RAJIV SAXENA
description: Sakshi Gupta, an ICICI Bank relationship manager in Kota, has been arrested for allegedly embezzling Rs 4.6 crore from 110 accounts between 2020 and 2023. She manipulated account details, rerouting transaction alerts and OTPs to her relatives while making unauthorized stock market investments.
title: ICICI manager ploughed Rs 4.6 crore customer funds into stocks, held

author: TNN
description: Canadian PM Mark Carney defended inviting Narendra Modi to the G7 summit, citing India's economic significance and its role in global supply chains. Despite ongoing concerns regarding the Hardeep Singh Nijjar case, Carney highlighted progress in law enforcement dialogue, emphasizing Canada's commitment to the rule of law.
title: India a must at G7 table: Mark Carney on inviting PM Modi

author: TNN
description: Bikaner police have arrested Shribhagwan, a 50-year-old man, for allegedly raping two minor sisters, aged 7 and 9. Investigations revealed a disturbing past, as Shribhagwan was previously convicted of murdering five family members during a 1993 robbery. Released in 2013, he lured the girls with promises before the assault, threatening them afterward.
title: Ex-convict who killed 5 in 1993 held again in Bikaner; had built temple on govt land
